---
import MainLayout from "../../layouts/MainLayout.astro";
---

<MainLayout
  title="Crate Training Guide - Stop Separation Anxiety Before It Starts"
  description="The 8-week protocol to eliminate separation anxiety and build calm independence. Used by Leash Legacy K9 in every Board & Train program."
>
  <!-- MAIN CONTENT -->
  <main class="max-w-6xl mx-auto px-4 py-16">
    <!-- HERO SECTION -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h1
          class="text-5xl md:text-6xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 leading-tight"
        >
          Your Dog Destroys the House When You Leave
        </h1>
        <p class="text-xl md:text-2xl text-gray-700 max-w-3xl mx-auto mb-4">
          The barking. The destruction. The guilt every time you walk out the
          door.
        </p>
        <p class="text-2xl font-bold text-red-600 mb-8">
          This isn't a "bad dog" problem. It's a training gap.
        </p>
        <div class="flex flex-col sm:flex-row gap-4 justify-center">
          <a
            href="#download"
            class="bg-yellow-500 hover:bg-yellow-600 text-gray-900 font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg transition transform hover:scale-105"
          >
            Get the Free 8-Week Protocol
          </a>
          <a
            href="#what-inside"
            class="bg-gray-900 hover:bg-gray-800 text-white font-bold px-8 py-4 rounded-full text-lg border-2 border-gray-900 transition"
          >
            See What's Inside
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE PROBLEM -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-red-50 py-16 px-8 rounded-2xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-8 text-center">
          Most Separation Anxiety Is Owner-Created
        </h2>

        <div
          class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-red-500 shadow-sm mb-8"
        >
          <p class="text-lg text-gray-900">
            <strong>Not intentionally. Not maliciously.</strong> But through:
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg
                class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Emotional Departures
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  "I'll be right back, be a good boy!" makes leaving a dramatic
                  event. Your dog learns: leaving = anxiety.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg
                class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Moving Too Fast</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Jumping from 5 minutes to 4 hours. Skipping the foundation
                  work. Pushing before your dog is ready.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg
                class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                  Inconsistent Routines
                </h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  Only crating when you leave. Making the crate a "you're
                  leaving" signal instead of a normal part of the day.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-sm">
            <div class="flex items-start gap-3">
              <svg
                class="w-6 h-6 text-red-600 flex-shrink-0 mt-1"
                fill="currentColor"
                viewBox="0 0 20 20"
              >
                <path
                  fill-rule="evenodd"
                  d="M10 18a8 8 0 100-16 8 8 0 000 16zM8.707 7.293a1 1 0 00-1.414 1.414L8.586 10l-1.293 1.293a1 1 0 101.414 1.414L10 11.414l1.293 1.293a1 1 0 001.414-1.414L11.414 10l1.293-1.293a1 1 0 00-1.414-1.414L10 8.586 8.707 7.293z"
                  clip-rule="evenodd"></path>
              </svg>
              <div>
                <h3 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Giving Up Too Soon</h3>
                <p class="text-gray-700">
                  "My dog hates the crate" after 2 days. Progress takes 8 weeks.
                  Most people quit at Week 3.
                </p>
              </div>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div class="bg-red-100 border-2 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-xl">
          <p class="text-xl text-red-900 font-bold">
            Here's what actually happens: <span class="block mt-2"
              >You come home to destroyed furniture, angry neighbors, and a
              panicked dog. Every failed departure reinforces the anxiety you're
              trying to stop.</span
            >
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- REAL CLIENT STORY -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-br from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-10 rounded-2xl border-2 border-blue-200"
        >
          <div class="text-center mb-6">
            <span class="text-5xl mb-4 block">🐕</span>
            <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
              "My dog screamed for 45 minutes straight every time I left."
            </h3>
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-700 italic">
              That was Duke's owner 8 weeks ago.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl mb-6">
            <p class="text-gray-800 mb-4">
              <strong>Today?</strong> Duke settles in his crate in under 2 minutes.
              Zero barking. Zero panic. Zero guilt.
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-800">
              <strong>What changed?</strong> She stopped winging it and started following
              a protocol.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div class="text-center">
            <p class="text-lg text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              The same protocol we're giving you for free below.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- THE SOLUTION -->
    <section class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          What You Actually Need
        </h2>

        <div
          class="bg-blue-50 rounded-2xl shadow-xl p-10 mb-12 border-2 border-blue-200"
        >
          <div class="text-center mb-8">
            <div class="text-6xl mb-4">📖</div>
            <h3 class="text-3xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
              The Complete Crate Training Protocol
            </h3>
            <p class="text-xl text-gray-700 mb-4">
              <strong>8 weeks. Step-by-step. Zero guessing.</strong>
            </p>
            <p class="text-gray-600 italic">
              Not generic advice. The exact system we use in our Board & Train
              programs to prevent separation anxiety in every single dog.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- Three Column Value Props -->
        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-3 gap-8">
          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-green-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🧠</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Nervous System Work
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Teach your dog that being alone is safe. Not just tolerable —
              safe. The foundation that prevents panic.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-blue-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">⏱️</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Weekly Progressions
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              Know exactly what to do each week. Door closes for 5 seconds → 1
              minute → 5 minutes → actual departures. Build right.
            </p>
          </div>

          <div
            class="feature-card bg-white p-8 rounded-xl shadow-md border-t-4 border-purple-500"
          >
            <div class="text-5xl mb-4">🛠️</div>
            <h3 class="text-xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-3">
              Troubleshooting Guide
            </h3>
            <p class="text-gray-700">
              "My dog barks nonstop." "My dog tries to escape." "My dog
              eliminates in the crate." We cover all of it.
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHAT'S INSIDE -->
    <section id="what-inside" class="mb-20">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          Inside This Free Guide
        </h2>

        <!-- WEEK 1 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-blue-50 to-blue-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-blue-600 mb-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🔵 WEEK 1: The Crate Is the Best Place in the House
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            Goal: Your dog voluntarily enters and hangs out with the door open
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Treat toss protocol</strong> — 3x daily, no pressure
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Feed meals inside</strong> — building positive association
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Chew toy sessions</strong> — voluntary entering and staying
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Common mistake:</strong> Closing the door too early (we prevent
              this)
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- WEEK 2 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-green-50 to-emerald-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-green-600 mb-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🟢 WEEK 2: Door Closes (But You're Right There)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            Goal: Dog stays calm with door closed while you're visible
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>5-second closes</strong> → 10 seconds → 30 seconds → 1 minute
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>The quiet rule:</strong> Never open during whining (critical)
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Progression guide</strong> — when to increase duration
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Red flags:</strong> When you're moving too fast
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- WEEK 3 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-yellow-50 to-amber-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-yellow-600 mb-6"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🟡 WEEK 3: You Move Away (But Stay in Sight)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            Goal: Dog stays calm while you move around the room
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>1 step back</strong> → 3 steps → across room → leave for 10
              seconds
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Natural movement practice</strong> — fold laundry, check phone
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>The critical rule:</strong> Return before panic starts
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>High-value chews</strong> — keeping your dog occupied
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- WEEK 4 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-r from-purple-50 to-purple-100 p-8 rounded-xl border-l-4 border-purple-600 mb-8"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4">
            🟣 WEEK 4: You Leave the Room (Short Departures)
          </h3>
          <p class="text-gray-700 mb-4 font-semibold">
            Goal: Dog stays calm when you leave the room briefly
          </p>
          <ul class="space-y-2 ml-6">
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>30 seconds</strong> → 2 minutes → 5 minutes → 15 minutes
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Boring departures:</strong> No "I'll be right back" drama
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Boring returns:</strong> No "I missed you so much" excitement
            </li>
            <li class="text-gray-800">
              ✓ <strong>Random crating:</strong> So it's not just a "leaving" signal
            </li>
          </ul>
        </div>

        <!-- MONTH 2 -->
        <div
          class="bg-gradient-to-br from-orange-50 to-red-100 p-10 rounded-2xl border-2 border-orange-300 mb-12"
        >
          <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
            🔥 MONTH 2: Building Real-World Independence
          </h3>

          <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6">
            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Week 5-6: Actual Departures
              </h4>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• You leave the house (5-30 minutes)</li>
                <li>• Desensitizing departure triggers</li>
                <li>• Variable durations (no patterns)</li>
                <li>• Wait 5 minutes before opening crate</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Week 7-8: Extended Absences
              </h4>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• 1-2 hour sessions</li>
                <li>• 3-4 hour comfort zone</li>
                <li>• Exercise before crating</li>
                <li>• Entertainment setup (Kongs, chews)</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">Advanced Topics</h4>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• Using crate throughout the day</li>
                <li>• Daily schedule examples</li>
                <li>• Transitioning away from crate</li>
                <li>• Lifetime maintenance</li>
              </ul>
            </div>

            <div>
              <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-2">
                Special Considerations
              </h4>
              <ul class="space-y-1 text-sm text-gray-800 ml-4">
                <li>• Rescue dogs & crate trauma</li>
                <li>• Puppies vs. adult dogs</li>
                <li>• When to get professional help</li>
                <li>• Success stories & timelines</li>
              </ul>
            </div>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- TROUBLESHOOTING SECTION -->
        <h3 class="text-2xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-6 text-center">
          ⭐ Complete Troubleshooting Guide Included
        </h3>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-4 mb-12">
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ "My Dog Barks Nonstop in the Crate"
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
              Learned behavior vs. actual anxiety + exact fix
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ "My Dog Tries to Escape/Breaks the Crate"
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
              Severe anxiety protocol + when to get help
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ "My Dog Eliminates in the Crate"
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
              Bladder limits + medical vs. behavioral issues
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-gray-50 p-4 rounded-lg">
            <p class="text-gray-900 font-semibold">
              ✓ "Calm in Crate But Anxious When I Leave"
            </p>
            <p class="text-sm text-gray-600 mt-1">
              Separation anxiety vs. crate training difference
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <!-- BONUS CONTENT -->
        <div class="bg-blue-50 border-2 border-blue-300 p-8 rounded-xl">
          <h4 class="font-bold text-gray-900 mb-4 text-xl">
            📋 Plus: Complete Checklists & Protocols
          </h4>
          <ul class="space-y-2 text-gray-800">
            <li>✓ Before You Start Checklist</li>
            <li>✓ Weekly Progress Trackers (Weeks 1-4, Month 2)</li>
            <li>✓ Red Flags & When to Get Professional Help</li>
            <li>✓ Equipment Guide (Wire vs. Plastic, Sizing)</li>
            <li>✓ Real Client Success Stories</li>
            <li>✓ The Leash Legacy K9 Mindset (Why This Works)</li>
          </ul>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- WHO IT'S FOR -->
    <section class="mb-20 bg-gray-50 py-16 px-8 rounded-2xl">
      <div class="max-w-4xl mx-auto">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold text-gray-900 mb-12 text-center">
          This Guide Is For You If...
        </h2>

        <div class="grid md:grid-cols-2 gap-6 mb-8">
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>Your dog panics when you leave</strong> (barking, destruction,
              pacing)
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You've tried crate training</strong> but it "didn't work"
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You feel guilty</strong> every time you walk out the door
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You want your dog to be calm alone</strong> — not just tolerating
              it
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You're willing to invest 8 weeks</strong> to fix this for life
            </p>
          </div>
          <div class="bg-white p-6 rounded-xl shadow-md flex items-start gap-4">
            <span class="text-3xl">✅</span>
            <p class="text-gray-900">
              <strong>You want a protocol</strong> — not random YouTube tips
            </p>
          </div>
        </div>

        <div
          class="bg-red-50 border-2 border-red-500 p-8 rounded-xl text-center"
        >
          <p class="text-gray-900 mb-2">
            <strong>This is NOT for you if:</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-gray-700">
            You're looking for a quick fix or a way to skip the foundation work.
            This takes 8 weeks of consistent effort. But it works.
          </p>
        </div>
      </div>
    </section>

    <!-- DOWNLOAD SECTION -->
    <section
      id="download"
      class="mb-20 hero-gradient text-white py-20 px-4 rounded-2xl"
    >
      <div class="max-w-2xl mx-auto text-center">
        <h2 class="text-4xl font-bold mb-6">
          Ready to Stop the Panic and Build Calm Independence?
        </h2>
        <p class="text-xl mb-4 text-purple-100">
          Download the complete 8-week Crate Training Protocol — the same system
          we use in our Board & Train programs.
        </p>
        <p class="text-lg mb-10 text-purple-100 italic">
          Week-by-week. Step-by-step. Zero guessing.
        </p>

        <div
          class="bg-white/10 backdrop-blur p-10 rounded-2xl border-2 border-white/20"
        >
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold mb-6">
            Enter your email below for instant access:
          </p>

          <!-- REPLACE WITH YOUR ACTUAL TALLY FORM -->
          <iframe
            data-tally-src="https://tally.so/embed/lbdAOp?alignLeft=1&hideTitle=1&transparentBackground=1&dynamicHeight=1"
            loading="lazy"
            width="100%"
            height="1110"
            frameborder="0"
            marginheight="0"
            marginwidth="0"
            title="Crate-Training Guide Download"></iframe>
          <script>
            var d = document,
              w = "https://tally.so/widgets/embed.js",
              v = function () {
                "undefined" != typeof Tally
                  ? Tally.loadEmbeds()
                  : d
                      .querySelectorAll("iframe[data-tally-src]:not([src])")
                      .forEach(function (e) {
                        e.src = e.dataset.tallySrc;
                      });
              };
            if ("undefined" != typeof Tally) v();
            else if (d.querySelector('script[src="' + w + '"]') == null) {
              var s = d.createElement("script");
              ((s.src = w),
                (s.onload = v),
                (s.onerror = v),
                d.body.appendChild(s));
            }
          </script>

          <p class="text-sm text-purple-200 mt-6">
            We'll send the guide to your email immediately. No spam, no selling
            your info.
          </p>
        </div>

        <div class="mt-12">
          <p class="text-lg font-semibold mb-4">
            <strong>Need Hands-On Support?</strong>
          </p>
          <p class="text-purple-100 mb-6">
            Our Board & Train programs include intensive crate training and
            separation anxiety prevention — plus handler transfer coaching so
            the progress sticks.
          </p>
          <a
            href="https://leashlegacyk9.com/programs/board-train/"
            class="inline-block bg-white text-purple-600 font-bold px-10 py-4 rounded-full hover:bg-gray-100 transition"
          >
            Learn About Our Board & Train Program →
          </a>
        </div>
      </div>
